    "installation_torque": "85 ft-lbs for future/annual inspections",
    "installation_steps": [
      "Drill hole perpendicular to work surface, do not ream or allow wobble",
      "Drill hole deeper than intended embedment, not closer than 2 anchor diameters to bottom",
      "Clean hole using compressed air and nylon brush",
      "Ensure spear heads are located against wedge pockets",
      "Turn nut until contact with top of spears and bottom of washer, insert into hole",
      "Tap anchor into hole with 2.5 lb hammer until washer rests solidly against fixture",
      "Tighten nut not less than 3 full turns but not more than 5 turns past hand tight"
    ],
    "important": "Do NOT use impact wrench for installation"
  },
  "notes": [
    "This is the same slab requirements document that appears in parallelogram-lifts and specialty-items directories",
    "ACI Temp only means floor must be properly aged to American Concrete Institute specifications",
    "Minimum 4x4x10/10 wire mesh is recommended for ACI Temp only models",
    "Main reinforcing and lower temperature steel shall be Grade 60 deformed bars",
    "Bar spacing tolerance is +/- 1 inch",
    "New slabs must be 12 inches thick minimum",
    "New slab must be totally surrounded by existing concrete floor",
    "New slab design is stand-alone and does not account for surrounding concrete contribution",
